# Charm Payments — Master Cursor Rule

You are working on Charm Payments — a merchant payment processing platform built on the Finto HTML template, deployed via GitHub to Vercel at charm-payments.vercel.app.

## IDENTITY
- Product: Charm Payments — merchant payment processing (not a bank, not a consumer wallet)
- Users: Small and mid-size business owners
- Stack: Finto HTML + vanilla JS + Bootstrap + Remixicon + scrollCue
- Gateway: NMI with First Data/Fiserv acquiring
- Brand: Primary #0c3a30 (dark green) · Accent #9edd05 (lime green)
- Email: merchants@charmpayments.com
- Phone: +1 (314) 555-0198
- Copyright: © Charm Payments — A Charm Holdings LLC Company

## NEVER DO THIS
- Never rename or remove Finto CSS class names
- Never use hello@finto.com or +001 (808) 5550148 or HiBootstrap
- Never use "Finto - Fintech, Banking, & Finance HTML Template" as a page title
- Never add dropdown menus to the navbar — flat 5-link nav only
- Never hardcode absolute URLs — all asset paths are relative
- Never commit broken internal links

## ALWAYS DO THIS
- Every page title: "[Page Name] — Charm Payments"
- Every page uses the STANDARD NAV and STANDARD FOOTER defined below
- Every page mentioning payment processing includes the compliance disclaimer
- Icons use Remixicon ri- classes only
- External links: target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"
- Images: descriptive alt text; decorative: alt="" aria-hidden="true"
- One H1 per page

## COMPLIANCE DISCLAIMER (required on every page mentioning payment processing)
"Charm Payments is a payment facilitator, not a bank. Payment processing services are provided through our licensed acquiring bank partner. Merchant funds are subject to the terms of the Merchant Agreement."

## COPY RULES
- 8th grade reading level max
- Never: "unhackable", "guaranteed approval", "lowest rates in the industry"
- CTAs must be descriptive: "Apply for Your Merchant Account" not "Submit"
- Rate claims must be specific and complete

## SEO
- Title: "[Page Name] — Charm Payments"
- Meta description: 150-160 chars, merchant search intent
- One H1 per page, never skip heading levels H1 > H2 > H3

